Tasked with managing HR strategy and L&D functionality for a branch of Investec, I provided subject matter expertise and direction to the development and execution of a strategic roadmap for HR. Focused on achieving maximum results for a workforce of 300 front and back office asset management and support professionals, I drove the establishment of a continuous improvement culture to drive proactive identification of risks and opportunities. A large part of this role focused on improving recruitment and selection processes for over 40 vacancies a month while also driving the adoption of best practice solutions across the business. 

KEY ACHIEVEMENTS
•	Reduced time to recruit from 3 months to 6 weeks, improving relationships with recruitment agencies to elevate employer branding and pipeline high-quality talent for in-demand skill sets;
•	Secured approval to establish Pretoria State’s only corporate subsidised crèche, focused on retaining and facilitating a workforce comprised of 70% young females;
•	Introduced an Induction Program targeted in socialising new recruits into the business while providing cost effective, intense two-day training program;
•	Designed and rolled out an employee referral program to improve access to passive and active talent pools.

